  "scenes": [
    {
      "type": "title-card",
      "duration": 4,
      "data": {
        "title": "Building a React Component",
        "subtitle": "Step-by-step walkthrough with live explanations",
        "date": "April 2026"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code-terminal-with-captions",
      "duration": 12,
      "data": {
        "title": "Creating a Custom Hook",
        "shell": "zsh",
        "captionPosition": "right",
        "steps": [
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "touch useCounter.ts" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "" },
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "cat > useCounter.ts << 'EOF'" }
            ],
            "caption": "First, we create a new file and start writing our custom hook using a TypeScript template."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "output", "text": "import { useState } from 'react';" },
              { "kind": "blank", "text": "" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "export function useCounter(initialValue = 0) {" }
            ],
            "caption": "We import <code>useState</code> from React and define our hook with an optional initial value parameter."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "output", "text": "  const [count, setCount] = useState(initialValue);" },
              { "kind": "blank", "text": "" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "  const increment = () => setCount(c => c + 1);" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "  const decrement = () => setCount(c => c - 1);" }
            ],
            "caption": "The hook maintains <strong>count</strong> state and provides two methods: <code>increment</code> and <code>decrement</code>."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "output", "text": "  const reset = () => setCount(initialValue);" },
              { "kind": "blank", "text": "" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "  return { count, increment, decrement, reset };" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "}" }
            ],
            "caption": "We add a <strong>reset</strong> method and return all the state and handlers as an object."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "output", "text": "EOF" },
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "cat useCounter.ts" },
              { "kind": "success", "text": "✓ Hook created successfully" }
            ],
            "caption": "The hook is complete and ready to use in your React components! Save and verify the file."
          }
        ]
      },
      "animation": {
        "easing": "easeOut",
        "delay": 0.2
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "code-terminal-with-captions",
      "duration": 10,
      "data": {
        "title": "Using the Hook",
        "shell": "bash",
        "captionPosition": "below",
        "steps": [
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "npx create-react-app my-counter-app" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "Creating a new React app..." },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "Initialized empty Git repository" }
            ],
            "caption": "First, we create a new React application using Create React App."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "cd my-counter-app && npm start" },
              { "kind": "success", "text": "✓ Starting development server on port 3000" }
            ],
            "caption": "Navigate to the project and start the development server to see changes in real-time."
          },
          {
            "lines": [
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "cp ../useCounter.ts src/" },
              { "kind": "prompt", "text": "cat src/App.tsx" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "// Updated to use useCounter hook" },
              { "kind": "output", "text": "const { count, increment, decrement } = useCounter(0);" }
            ],
            "caption": "Copy the hook to your project and import it in your components to start using it."
          }
        ]
      },
      "transition": "fade"
    },
    {
